<br>
Its cool to see how fast you move, even for so brief a period of time. And the casting time is what, zero?<br>
<br>
Anyway, just wondering if anyone uses this on a regular basis, or keeps it memd somewhere at the bottom, in case of an emergency. And please don't tell me I shouldn't waste the plat on it, cause I already did :)<br>
<br>
<br>
-Montresor<br>
27th season Druid<br>
Vazaelle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uellendilhsilvermist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellendilh Silvermist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/21/01 4:30:43 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~phiphix/FAlogo-MB3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spirit of cheetah</span><hr size=1> Very situational spell. <br>
<br>
Basically, in situations where you might be dispelled by mobs. Skyfire or PoF (if you pull) comes to mind. Other than that, no too much to worry about. Furthermore if you have JBoots, which are inta-cast anyway and can replace a dispelled sow.<br>
<br>
The recast time is so long because, otherwise, people would you it all the time.... VI's logic is unbeatable.... <p><p><HR>
