<br>
;) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uligge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ligge</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/23/01 8:35:05 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.eqguide.com/images/vermsmall.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spirit of cheetah</span><hr size=1> 58 levels - 160 played days - used this spell twice, once just to see how fast it really made me and the other because it was memmed already and I used it to fly from NK port to bridge<br>
<br>
Its always been pretty much worthless to me. Your mileage may vary. :) <p><p><font face="Trebuchet MS, Tahoma" size="1"><a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=6031>Ligge</a> - Changing Tide CoGuildleader<br><font color=green><a href="http://pub17.ezboard.com/beqguide">Changing Tide's Boards</a><b> || </b><a href="http://pub2.ezboard.com/bthefolk">The Folk's Boards</a></font><br><b>"You must be the change you wish to see in the world." - Mahatma Ghandi</b><br>"Never argue with an idiot. They drag you down to their level then beat you with experience."</font></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueyeds.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eyeds</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/23/01 4:19:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spirit of cheetah</span><hr size=1> Before it was nerfed a year ago it was very useful for long runs.  It was refreshing as soon as you zoned, so you cast it port into a zone run like hell, it worre off, recast make it to zone, recast run some more etc.  Why they nerfed it I will never know. <p>Eyed <BR>
Visions <BR>
Lanys T'Vyl <BR>
58 Preserver</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uperkynipples.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Perk Ynipples</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/24/01 12:56:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spirit of cheetah</span><hr size=1> I'm probably different for 95% of other druids...  Anytime I'm outdoors, and most druids would normally have gate up... I have Cheetah up.  Simple reason for this is the cast time... I've got a much better chance of getting a .5 second cast off than a 5.0 second cast off.  SoC lasts only 30 seconds, but you have such ass hauling speed for 30 seconds, that you'll have plenty of time to mem gate or egress and hit it to clear agro. Saves my ass in bad situations at least twice a week... (of course I'd do better to avoid those situations... but its just amazing all the places people expect me to port them out of.. &quot;You expect me to pick you up where?&quot;  &quot;Um ToV please... oh and Sontalak is up&quot; =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umaani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maani</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/24/01 1:28:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spirit of cheetah</span><hr size=1> i use this spell loads getting over west karnana cause its soooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooo long a run to qeynos .. they badly need a druid ring in everfrost :p<br>
<br>
<br>
maani<br>
55 drooid on povar<br>
guild innit <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=drew>Drew</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/30/01 8:32:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Nerfed</span><hr size=1> <br>
   SoC was meant to be escape.  It was almost entirely used as a travel spell in practice, though, the more so since it would refresh when you zoned.  SoC right before the zone, carry on at Cheetah speed while it lasted, and SoC again when it drops.  You could really move.<br>
<br>
   Naturally, Verant hated the fact that someone used the spell for something other than their intent.  So, they nerfed the recast delay (which isn't affected by zoning).  As with any spell, you've got to wait through the recast when you first mem it.  And with SoC, it takes forever.  So, you've got to either burn a slot on it 100% of the time, or never use it.  Post-nerf, it's pretty much in the never-used pile.  Too many other spells demanding a slot, and too little need for it.<br>
<br>
   There's probably a couple of places you might press it into service, fighting SoW-speed mobs, but druids seem to manage without for the most part.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urhesolooshun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhes Olooshun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/31/01 10:08:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nerfed</span><hr size=1> The only zone that I actually use this spell is when I am soloing in Skyfire.  I load this spell in my bottom-most slot and use it when I get dispelled pulling named Chromodrachs and lose Form of the Howler.  It has saved my butt on numerous occaisions, and is well worth the used slot as the only spells I really use in this zone after initial buffing are Ensnare, Engorging Roots, Winged Death, Breath of Karana, Improved Superior Camo for pulling and Chloroblast, so I have plenty of slots left over for utilities such as this. <p><a href="http://worldzone.net/"target="web"><img src="http://worldzone.net/themes/azyn//sig2.GIF"border="0"</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urhesolooshun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhes Olooshun</A> at: 7/31/01 10:09:28 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvonkaar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>vonkaar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(8/1/01 3:17:09 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://vonkaar.homestead.com/files/vonk-brad.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nerfed</span><hr size=1> It no longer overrides form of the howler.  Found that out last night in WW.  Cast it, your spell does not hold etc etc, and it counts as  being cast for the recast delay.<br>
<br>
Thanks. <p><BR>
