</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urhesolooshun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhes Olooshun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(8/1/01 4:13:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nerfed</span><hr size=1> Never said it did.....I said I used it when my wolf form gets dispelled as an escape spell.......=) <p><a href="http://worldzone.net/"target="web"><img src="http://worldzone.net/themes/azyn//sig2.GIF"border="0"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzestrenocya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zestrenocya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(8/1/01 9:48:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spirit of cheetah</span><hr size=1> Uses for cheetah in my experience:<br>
<br>
1--Running like hell for the mistmoore zone (or any zone for that matter) when, for some reason, you didn't want to evac.<br>
<br>
2--Pulling in fear.  (That's about the only time I still keep it mem'd, and I usually only pull the amy temple now if I pull at all.)<br>
<br>
3--Speed boost for a long zone like WK pre nerf.<br>
<br>
But I've cast it many times...and it has, occassionally, saved my arse. <p><BR>
